<div class="container">
    <h2>About Our Project</h2>
    <p>The Climate Story project aims to provide an engaging platform that highlights the pressing issue of climate change in Canada. By utilizing publicly available data from the Government of Canada, we aim to present real-time insights into CO2 emissions and their impacts on our environment.</p>

    <p>Our interactive map allows users to visualize CO2 emissions across various regions, making it easier to understand the geographical disparities in emissions and the challenges they pose. Additionally, the 'Stories' section delves into real-world examples of how climate change affects wildlife, agriculture, and communities across the country.</p>

    <p>We hope to raise awareness and encourage action toward a sustainable future by presenting these critical insights in an accessible format. Join us in our journey to understand and combat climate change!</p>
</div>

<div class="container mt-5">
    <h2 class="text-center">How You Can Help</h2>
    <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item">📚 <strong>Educate Yourself and Others:</strong> Learn about climate change and share your knowledge.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">🌱 <strong>Reduce Your Carbon Footprint:</strong> Use public transport, reduce energy consumption, and minimize waste.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">🛍️ <strong>Support Sustainable Practices:</strong> Buy local and choose sustainable products.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">🤝 <strong>Get Involved in Local Initiatives:</strong> Volunteer for environmental conservation projects in your community.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">📢 <strong>Advocate for Policy Changes:</strong> Contact your representatives to support climate-friendly policies.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">📝 <strong>Resources:</strong> Visit our <a href="/Home/Resources">Resources</a> page to find organizations you can connect with.</li>
    </ul>
</div>
